    "description": "Across a cobbled street from the 16th-century Sokollu Mehmed Pasha Mosque, this traditional Turkish hotel in a colorful Ottoman house is a 14-minute walk from the Byzantine-era church, Hagia Sophia, and the bustling Grand Bazaar marketplace. Çemberlitaş metro station is 8 minutes' on foot.\n Plush air-conditioned rooms with carved wood furnishings offer free Wi-Fi, flat-screen TVs and minibars, plus tea and coffeemaking facilities. They also provide in-room safes, bottled water and soundproof windows.\n Continental breakfast is available. There's also a lobby lounge, and a tour desk which can arrange airport transfers.",
